<headline>Special Weather Statement issued December 14 at 7:40AM PST  by NWS Portland</headline>
<description>...ISOLATED SNOW SHOWERS AND ICY ROADS TO IMPACT THE MORNING
COMMUTE...
Isolated showers this morning will once again allow snow to fall
and accumulate on elevated and grassy surfaces. On roads it should
generally remain more slushy. However, freezing air temperatures
and some freezing road temperatures may allow black ice to form,
especially on bridges and overpasses. Expect spotty snow
accumulations of up to an additional half inch this morning.
Temperatures should warm above freezing by mid-morning.</description>
